  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba4 \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba3\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0ba9 !",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Train fares are increasing!",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Railway Department has announced that the train fares will be increased with effect from midnight tomorrow.",
        "In June, the cabinet gave its nod to a proposal to hike fares and other rail charges.",
        "The Government has informed that due to increase in fuel prices, the railway department is not able to provide adequate services due to the increase in traffic.",
        "Accordingly, the railway fares have been revised with effect from midnight tomorrow.",
        "Accordingly, the initial fee for first and second class has been revised to 50 rupees and the initial fee for third class has been revised to 20 rupees."
      ],
